title: José Pacini
text:
José Mauricio Pacini (born 8 June 1976) is an <a href="Argentina">Argentine</a> <a href="Association%20football">football</a> player who most recently played for <a href="Platense%20F.C.">Platense F.C.</a> in the <a href="Liga%20Nacional%20de%20Honduras">Honduran national league</a>.
Club career.
He played in Honduras for several years. He started his career at <a href="Pumas%20UNAH">Universidad</a> in <a href="1999-2000%20Honduran%20Liga%20Nacional">1999-2000 Apertura</a>. Later he played for <a href="C.D.S.%20Vida">Vida</a>, <a href="Platense%20F.C.">C.D. Platense</a>, <a href="F.C.%20Motagua">F.C. Motagua</a>, <a href="C.D.%20Marath%C3%B3n">Marathón</a>, <a href="Real%20C.D.%20Espa%C3%B1a">Real España</a>, <a href="C.D.%20Victoria">Victoria</a>, and <a href="C.D.%20Olimpia">Olimpia</a>, winning the title with Platense in 2001 (<a href="2000-01%20Honduran%20Liga%20Nacional">2000-01 Clausura</a>), with Motagua in 2001 (<a href="2001-02%20Honduran%20Liga%20Nacional">2001-02 Apertura</a>), and with Marathón in 2003 (<a href="2002-03%20Honduran%20Liga%20Nacional">2002-03 Clausura</a>). 
Pacini also participated in international club competition for several Honduran clubs, scoring for Motagua in qualifying for the <a href="2003%20CONCACAF%20Champions%27%20Cup">2003 CONCACAF Champions' Cup</a>, for Marathón in the preliminary stages of the <a href="2004%20CONCACAF%20Champions%27%20Cup">2004 CONCACAF Champions' Cup</a>, and for Olimpia in the quarter final stage of the <a href="2007%20CONCACAF%20Champions%27%20Cup">2007 CONCACAF Champions' Cup</a>. In <a href="Argentina">Argentina</a>, he played in some clubs such as <a href="Guillermo%20Brown%20de%20Puerto%20Madryn">Guillermo Brown de Puerto Madryn</a> and <a href="Defensores%20de%20Belgrano">Defensores de Belgrano</a> before returning to Honduras in 2011.
